# Local development environment overrides.
# Copy from env/.env.example and adjust values; this file is loaded only when your tooling points at it.

# =========================
# vet-microservices stack (optional)
# =========================
# When you run Vet-AI from ``vet-microservices/docker-compose.yml``, copy or symlink env into
# ``vet-microservices/.env.local`` (compose loads it for ``vet-ai`` / ``genai-service``).
# Align at least:
#   MLAIR_API_BASE_URL=http://mlair-api:8080
#   MLAIR_AUTH_TOKEN = ML_AIR_TRACKING_TOKEN on mlair-api (default in compose: admin-token)
#   ML_AIR_WORKER_TOKEN = same token if you use external task mode + Vet-AI worker
#   MLAIR_PIPELINE_ID = pipeline id that exists in MLAir for that tenant/project (see POST /mlair/models/sync)
# Host-only: NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL for mlair-frontend should point at published ML_AIR_API_PORT (default 8080).
